com.addith.view

Interface ViewStrategy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Observer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConsoleStrategy, GuiStrategy

    public interface ViewStrategy
extends java.util.Observer
    "Strategy" interface; part of the Strategy Design Pattern. We use the strategy pattern to define view, so additional view types can be added easily for the same back end. It declares an interface common to all supported views. View Context uses this interface to launch the view defined by a Concrete view Strategy. This interface also implements Observer as part of the Observer Design Pattern. Observer design pattern is used for the run time updates to the view console without having to wait for the process to finish. Design Pattern: Observer, Strategy
